		<h3>Governor Extends School Closure to May 15<br>
</h3>
		
		
		
		
		
			<p class="summary">"New York Governor Andrew Cuomo announced that statewide state-at-home measures will continue through May 15, 2020. This means that Valhalla Schools will remain closed until at least that date. The governor extended the shutdown in partnership with six nearby northeast states."</p>
		
		
		
			<span class="text rteSpan"><div>Dear Valhalla families,</div>
<br><div>We hope that you are all doing well at home. We miss seeing you on campus and interacting as a community. While working remotely can sometimes be difficult, together <strong>we are Viking Strong</strong> and are grateful that we’re all doing our part to help “flatten the curve” and lessen the spread of coronavirus.</div>
<br><div>
<strong>New York Governor Andrew Cuomo announced that statewide state-at-home measures will continue through May 15, 2020.</strong> This means that Valhalla Schools will remain closed until at least that date. The governor extended the shutdown in partnership with six nearby northeast states.</div>
<br><div>Please remember that Grab and Go Lunches are available at Virginia Road School and Valhalla Middle/High School from 11 a.m. to 1 p.m. Families may utilize whichever school is in proximity to them. Additionally, childcare services for first responders and essential personnel will continue to be available at Easter Seals. For additional childcare information, please call 914-261-1889.</div>
<br><div>Stay well,</div>
<br><div><strong>Christina Howe,</strong></div>
<div><em>Interim Superintendent</em></div>
<div><em>Valhalla Schools</em></div></span><br><div align="right">
		<br clear="both"><br>
</div>
		
		
		
	
		
		
		
		
		
